## 🔴 Critical Bugs (P0)

### Bug 1: Four Sidebar Links Lead to 404 Pages
- **Severity**: 🔴 Critical
- **Location**: [Sidebar.tsx](file:///Users/piyushsharma/Projects/Project%203%20Prior%20Auth%20Pipeline/src/components/dashboard/Sidebar.tsx#L23-L29)
- **Description**: The sidebar navigation includes links to 4 pages that have no corresponding `page.tsx` files:
  - `/console/analytics` — linked but no `src/app/console/analytics/page.tsx`
  - `/console/batch` — linked but no `src/app/console/batch/page.tsx`
  - `/console/manual` — linked but no `src/app/console/manual/page.tsx`
  - `/console/settings` — linked but no `src/app/console/settings/page.tsx`
- **Impact**: Users who click these nav items see a raw Next.js 404 page (completely unstyled, jarring)

### Bug 2: "Load Randomized Case" Button Silently Fails
- **Severity**: 🔴 Critical
- **Location**: [RequestForm.tsx](file:///Users/piyushsharma/Projects/Project%203%20Prior%20Auth%20Pipeline/src/components/dashboard/RequestForm.tsx#L42-L66)
- **Description**: The button calls `fetch(\`${baseUrl}/api/scenarios?count=1\`)` where `baseUrl` defaults to `http://localhost:8000`. In production on Vercel, there's no `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` env var set, and `localhost:8000` is unreachable. The `catch` block only does `console.error` — no user-facing feedback.
- **Impact**: Button click does nothing; all form fields remain empty; user has no idea why

### Bug 3: "Submit Authorization Request" Silently Fails
- **Severity**: 🔴 Critical
- **Location**: [RequestForm.tsx](file:///Users/piyushsharma/Projects/Project%203%20Prior%20Auth%20Pipeline/src/components/dashboard/RequestForm.tsx#L68-L97)
- **Description**: Same issue — `fetch(\`${baseUrl}/api/submit\`)` hits `localhost:8000` in production. The `catch` block does `alert("Pipeline Submission Error. Ensure backend is running.")` — but even this alert doesn't fire cleanly because the form allows submission with ALL empty fields (no validation).
- **Impact**: Users can submit a completely empty form. On Vercel, it fails silently or with a generic alert.

